Description: Bracelet or armlet: on the original twisted flax threads composed of twelve rows of beads, strung horizontally in vertical groups of three. The beads are hung in groups of three and are cylinders made of turquoise-blue, dark-blue, black and white glazed composition. The dark-blue beads are few in number and mixed indiscriminately with the black ones.
Curator's comments: Registered as coming from the same burial as 1905,1014.33 but not mentioned in the publication as being among the contents. Bibliography: E. Naville, 'The XIth Dynasty temple at Dier el-Bahari’ I (London, 1907) 45-6.
Bibliographic references: Andrews 1981 / Catalogue of Egyptian Antiquities. Jewellery I (392)
